          <p class='first-para'>
            Order. Under the rules of the House, it is necessary for hon. Members who wish to intervene to give prior notice to the hon.
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_60wh' title='Col. 60WH &mdash; HC Deb 18 June 2002 vol 387 c60WH' name='column_60wh' href='#column_60wh' rel='bookmark'>60WH</a>
            Member who has secured the Adjournment debate and the Minister who is responding, and for both of them to give their agreement to those interventions.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0387P1_20020618_WH_72'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-mark-todd' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
